==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Xylylene
<hw>Xy"lyl*ene</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>Any one of three metameric radicals, <chform>CH2.C6H4.CH2</chform>,
derived respectively from the three xylenes. Often used adjectively;
<as>as, <ex>xylylene</ex> alcohol</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Xyridaceous</ent>⟦br⟧
